\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. S. beirana} Samp.,{\i  Bol. Soc. Brot.} ser. 2, {\b 7}: 125 (1931). Bulb c. 25 mm in diameter, ovoid. Stems 30-40 cm. Leaves 3-6, 30-40 cm × 8-15 mm, linear-oblong, gradually narrowed at base and apex, acute, glabrous, the cauline exceeding the stem. Inflorescence 8-15 cm, racemose, 30 to 40-flowered; bracts 15-18 mm, subulate, entire; pedicels 18-25 mm, ascending to semi-patent. Perianth-segments 6-7 mm, bluish-violet. Filaments 1-1·2 mm wide, lanceolate. •{\i  N.E. Portugal} ({\i Beira Alta}). Lu.
